timeline.bodyText:
while the logic is correct, I don't want us to carry out additional work if not necessary. e.g. if the principal is not user there is no reason for us to check the expiry (it's just a wasted operation).
we should have logic implemented like this:
if (!roleMember.getMemberName().startsWith(userDomainPrefix)) {
return false;
}
return (roleMember.getExpiration() == null) || (roleMember.getExpiration().millis() > System.currentTimeMillis());

